252,"body":253,"divs":254,"editions":279,"images":289,"handnote":295},"ISic000230. Funerary inscription for Vecilia","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucia · Vecilia Lucii filia\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucia\">L(ucia)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Vecilia\">Vecilia\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucii\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Lucii\">L(ucii)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"filia\">f(ilia)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>vix(it) an(nis) XXX \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucia · Vecilia Lucii filia\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucia\">L\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Vecilia\">VECILIA\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucii\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Lucii\">L\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"filia\">F\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>VIXANXXX\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000230_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-08\" src=\"ISic000230_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000230.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-08\" src=\"ISic000230-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Castelli: VICILIA L. F\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Castelli: VIX. ANN. XXX.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Lucia Vecilia, daughter of Lucius, lived for 30 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Vecilia, unusually, has a praenomen, presumably adopted from her father, Lucius. Vecilii are well-attested in Thermae Himeraeae, see esp. \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000231\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000231\u003C/a>, \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000229\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000229\u003C/a>, and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000228\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000228\u003C/a>. Romano notes that Castelli's text, which was at second hand, was somewhat inaccurate.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 331 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Romano 1829 303 no.14 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002748\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002748\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">7444\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bivona 1994 155 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Text is only lightly inscribed on stone. Letters even spaced and well-formed. Light serifs. Graffiti very rough, grey scratches on surface. Letters are imitative of main text, but thickness of lines, size of letters and orientation of letters are inconsistent.\u003C/p> Line 1  36-41  Line 2  35-42  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[255,258,261,264,267,270,273,276],{"id":256,"html":257},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucia · Vecilia Lucii filia\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucia\">L(ucia)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Vecilia\">Vecilia\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucii\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Lucii\">L(ucii)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"filia\">f(ilia)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>vix(it) an(nis) XXX \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucia · Vecilia Lucii filia\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucia\">L\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Vecilia\">VECILIA\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucii\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Lucii\">L\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"filia\">F\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>VIXANXXX\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":259,"html":260},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000230_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-08\" src=\"ISic000230_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000230.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-08\" src=\"ISic000230-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":262,"html":263},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Castelli: VICILIA L. F\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Castelli: VIX. ANN. XXX.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":265,"html":266},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Lucia Vecilia, daughter of Lucius, lived for 30 years.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":268,"html":269},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Vecilia, unusually, has a praenomen, presumably adopted from her father, Lucius. Vecilii are well-attested in Thermae Himeraeae, see esp. \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000231\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000231\u003C/a>, \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000229\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000229\u003C/a>, and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000228\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000228\u003C/a>. Romano notes that Castelli's text, which was at second hand, was somewhat inaccurate.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":271,"html":272},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 331 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Romano 1829 303 no.14 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002748\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002748\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">7444\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bivona 1994 155 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":274,"html":275},"handnote","\u003Cp>Text is only lightly inscribed on stone. Letters even spaced and well-formed. Light serifs. Graffiti very rough, grey scratches on surface. Letters are imitative of main text, but thickness of lines, size of letters and orientation of letters are inconsistent.\u003C/p> Line 1  36-41  Line 2  35-42  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":277,"html":278},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[280,282,285,286],{"html":281},"Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou",{"id":283,"lang":132,"html":284},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucia · Vecilia Lucii filia\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucia\">L(ucia)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Vecilia\">Vecilia\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucii\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Lucii\">L(ucii)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"filia\">f(ilia)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>vix(it) an(nis) XXX \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":281},{"id":287,"lang":132,"html":288},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucia · Vecilia Lucii filia\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucia\">L\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Vecilia\">VECILIA\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucii\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Lucii\">L\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"filia\">F\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>VIXANXXX\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[290,292],{"image":107,"thumb":291,"title":110},"ISic000230_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":293,"thumb":294,"title":110},"ISic000230.jpg","ISic000230-thumb.jpg",[296],{"html":55},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Funerary inscription for Vecilia\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n        \u003CrespStmt>\n                 \u003Cname xml:id=\"VM\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511\">Valentina Mignosa\u003C/name>\n                 \u003Cresp>encoding text division and checking the edition\u003C/resp>\n        \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"AA\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>Edition on basis of autopsy and photographs\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic000230\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">285307\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\">127533\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">22100146\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000230\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-17\">10.5281/zenodo.4334660\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Termini Imerese\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/066\">Museo Civico Baldassare Romano\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">124\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Rectangular stele, grey limestone. Sides relatively squared, with chips on top and bottom faces. Rear tapers to flat surface. Significant later damage, including later graffiti scratched onto front face. Large scratches on front face.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.stele\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250\">stele\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">32\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">67.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">21\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Two lines of Latin text, roughly centred on stone, but all contained within top half of the stone. Small dash interpunct is evident in line 1, but possible traces elsewhere. Graffiti squeezed into stone between left edge of stone and start of text, and roughly follows lines of inscription (but far from faithfully).\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Text is only lightly inscribed on stone. Letters even spaced and well-formed. Light serifs. Graffiti very rough, grey scratches on surface. Letters are imitative of main text, but thickness of lines, size of letters and orientation of letters are inconsistent.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"36\" atMost=\"41\">36-41\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"35\" atMost=\"42\">35-42\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462513\">Thermae Himeraeae\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/6539140\">Termini Imerese\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.98365, 13.69555\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0001\" notAfter-custom=\"0050\">Bivona (1994, 239) dates to the first half of the 1st century CE based on the missing cognomen.\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1783\">Found in Termini Imerese in 1783 (so Castelli 1784), and in the local senate house collection by 1829 (Romano).\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" when=\"2022-07-08\" resp=\"#AA\">Antoniou, 2022-07-08. On display in the courtyard portico of Museo Civico Baldassare Romano\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                   \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n                   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-09\" who=\"#VM\">Valentina Mignosa encoded text division, cleaned up the autogenerated text and checked the edition\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n\t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-17\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2023-08-30\" who=\"#AA\">edition on basis of autopsy and photographs\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic000230_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-08\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic000230.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-08\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#VM #AA\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>L\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ucia\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>Vecilia\u003C/name> \u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname type=\"patronym\">\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>L\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ucii\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cw>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>f\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ilia\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/w>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>vix\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>it\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>an\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>nis\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cnum value=\"30\">XXX\u003C/num>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text from autopsy\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"1\">\u003Cnote>Castelli: VICILIA L. F\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"2\">\u003Cnote>Castelli: VIX. ANN. XXX.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003Cp>Lucia Vecilia, daughter of Lucius, lived for 30 years.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003Cp>Vecilia, unusually, has a praenomen, presumably adopted from her father, Lucius. Vecilii are well-attested in Thermae Himeraeae, see esp. \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000231\">ISic000231\u003C/ref>, \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000229\">ISic000229\u003C/ref>, and \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000228\">ISic000228\u003C/ref>. Romano notes that Castelli's text, which was at second hand, was somewhat inaccurate.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Castelli\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1784\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>331 no.4\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/7PSFHSUH\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Romano\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1829\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>303 no.14\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2UJS2UVS\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002748\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002748\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIL\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Mommsen\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1883\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>\n                            \u003Cref target=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\">7444\u003C/ref>\n                        \u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"ILMusTermini\">\n                         \u003Cauthor>Bivona\u003C/author>\n                         \u003Cdate>1994\u003C/date> \n                        \u003CcitedRange>155\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JCV85C79\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl/>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
